title: Capturing Packets in Linux at a Speed of Millions of Packets per Second without Using Third Party Libraries 
link: http://kukuruku.co/hub/nix/capturing-packets-in-linux-at-a-speed-of-millions-of-packets-per-second-without-using-third-party-libraries
tag: network perf, throughput
status: glimpse
summary:
1. Distribute Interrupts to Available Cores
2. solve lock issue via FANOUT, which distributes packets to local queue of each core.
3. solve buffer issue via RX_RING, which use cicular buffer.
